{
  "slide": 14,
  "duration": 61.78,
  "text": "What is this transformation? Well, paper is reactive and digital is proactive. With paper records, you've got your files logged on site, inside some filing cabinets. Digital makes all these records accessible from any device anyway for all stakeholders. Paper cannot prove what happened at 2 AM when you have that mock recall, where you've got that actual recall. But with digital, you provide time-stemmed, geolocated, photo-verified evidence. Paper, NCRs get lost or delayed in paper systems. Digital delivers automatic escalation. Paper needs your operations management to visit sites for visibility. What digital provides a combined center that is always on and that is available, trends available for all stakeholders.",
